      "urgency": "IMMEDIATE",
      "impact": "ORGANISM-WIDE",
      "priority_score": 10,
      "constitutional_attention_needed": "Human principal must author and ratify Articles I–VI to establish the DIO's core identity, immutable prohibitions, operational scope, human authority reservation, amendment process, and interpretation framework. Without this, the Bill of Rights cannot constrain the organism, rendering all downstream security and compliance measures rootless.",
      "why": "The Bill of Rights is the highest constitutional authority in the DIO. MSP §Relationship to the Bill of Rights declares any MSP rule conflicting with the BoR void; Arbiter (§190) verifies BoR hash on every scope query. With a null BoR content, the Arbiter will either fail closed (blocking all actions) or fail open (permitting unbounded enterprise), and there are no identity articles to ground the organism's 'self' — a direct conflict with the Mission Frame's requirement that the organism be defined by BoR identity articles."
