      "rationale": "The absence of any scope definition means all DIO actions are currently permissible by default, directly contravening the BoR's function as the supreme compliance boundary and violating the requirement that the enterprise perimeter be human-defined before operational authority is exercised."
    },
    {
      "gap_id": "GAP-BOR-002",
      "description": "Bill of Rights Article II – Prohibited Activities is empty. No activities are explicitly forbidden, meaning the DIO could undertake actions that a human principal might consider unacceptable (e.g., self-modification beyond safe bounds, external resource manipulation).",
      "grounding": {
        "document": "Bill of Rights",
        "section_article": "Article II — Prohibited Activities"
      },
      "priority": {
